{"TopicId":46131,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Conducting an entire mission in first-person mode","CreatedByName":"Masked Turk","CreatedById":76284,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-09-16T14:38:26Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Masked Turk","CreatedById":76284,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-09-16T14:38:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EAnyone ever tried it? I\u0027m talking about anything more than just orbiting, something like a Duna or Muna landing and return. I imagine it\u0027d be a way of adding new difficulty to the game for those who\u0027ve championed the challenging parts of KSP...\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rhomphaia","CreatedById":2440,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-09-16T14:50:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI have done a few IVA mun landings, but never the entire mission, only the final descent.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022480\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/dkO9WjoNHzc?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sapphire","CreatedById":67918,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-09-16T14:51:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EQueue KSP \u0022Manley Mode\u0022.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022480\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/p0c-gx03DpM?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEDIT: I wish SQUAD would hurry up and fix the forums so us Chrome users can post links and videosand photos and stuff... \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cry.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022;.;\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow88","CreatedById":66043,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-09-16T14:53:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EBit difficult to juggle a manoeuvre node from a first person perspective, unless you consider that as the first person perspective of the guy sitting at a navigation console back at control.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scotius","CreatedById":57622,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-09-16T15:16:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.projectrho.com/public_html/rocket/sealofapproval.php\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.projectrho.com/public_html/rocket/sealofapproval.php\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EJust scroll down to a part about KSP - there is amusing description of such mission flew by a group of fans. And they built honest-to-gosh Mission Control \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DaveSteadman","CreatedById":59314,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-09-16T15:24:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ESquad should make this a tough mode to keep experienced players challenged.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fiddlestyx","CreatedById":57329,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-09-16T15:33:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI tried it once, but don\u0027t know how to read the internal instruments so it didn\u0027t work. I did dock once IVA using docking cams, that was really fun.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Awaras","CreatedById":15671,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-09-16T15:40:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sapphire\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Sapphire\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EQueue KSP \u0022Manley Mode\u0022.\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022480\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/p0c-gx03DpM?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEDIT: I wish SQUAD would hurry up and fix the forums so us Chrome users can post links and videosand photos and stuff... \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cry.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022;.;\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhat do you mean? I use chrome and have not had any problems...\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHere\u0027s your video:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022480\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/p0c-gx03DpM?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"musicpenguin","CreatedById":57938,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-09-16T15:47:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EAlso i found you can post pictures on chrome by doing .\u003Cimg src=\u0022LINKHERE\u0022 alt=\u0022LINKHERE\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sapphire","CreatedById":67918,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-09-16T16:35:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Awaras\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Awaras\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EWhat do you mean? I use chrome and have not had any problems...\u003Cp\u003EHere\u0027s your video:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E-snip-\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENot for me... \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cry.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022;.;\u0022\u003E Look at my posting tools.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/3SOORx6.png\u0022 alt=\u00223SOORx6.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Awaras","CreatedById":15671,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-09-16T16:57:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sapphire\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Sapphire\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003ENot for me... \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cry.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022;.;\u0022\u003E Look at my posting tools.\u003Cp\u003E*snip*\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESo? Just use tags.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E{img}LINK{/img} for pictures\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E{video}LINK{/video} for youtube videos\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E{url=LINK}LINK DESCRIPTION{/url} for web links.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EJust replace {} with []\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHere is a more detailed description from the FAQ:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/showthread.php/48073-Forum-FAQ-%E2%80%93-Answers-for-New-Users?p=637094#post637094\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/showthread.php/48073-Forum-FAQ-%E2%80%93-Answers-for-New-Users?p=637094#post637094\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-09-16T17:01:25Z\u0022 title=\u002209/16/2013 05:01  PM\u0022 data-short=\u002210 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 16, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by Awaras\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lincourtl","CreatedById":72218,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-09-16T16:59:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sapphire\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Sapphire\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003ENot for me... \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cry.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022;.;\u0022\u003E Look at my posting tools.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E I have the same problem in Firefox. No visual editor. It started a couple of weeks ago. \u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/vdllyFO.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022vdllyFO.jpg\u0022\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"astropapi1","CreatedById":57507,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-09-16T17:02:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EUsing Kerbal Engineer would make it more realistic and easy. Might give it a go. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAnd MJ of course, for maneuver planning. Traveling in space without a map can be confusing.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-09-16T17:10:21Z\u0022 title=\u002209/16/2013 05:10  PM\u0022 data-short=\u002210 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 16, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by astropapi1\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"WafflesToo","CreatedById":71736,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-09-16T18:01:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWhen Scott did it he had a pre-planned flight profile and flew the mission using a stopwatch... the part of the mission that impressed me the most was when he went \u0022off-script\u0022 with that midflight course correction burn.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDon\u0027t get me wrong, the whole attempt was two-fisted awesome from beginning-to-end, that was just the most awesome.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"musicpenguin","CreatedById":57938,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-09-16T18:11:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EVery hard thing to do\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Klingon Admiral","CreatedById":69090,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-09-16T20:02:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rhomphaia\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Rhomphaia\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EI have done a few IVA mun landings, but never the entire mission, only the final descent.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn all honesty, I find IVA landings almost more easy than external view landings, at least when you know that the ground below you is relatively flat. The altimeter is just wonderful.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"rhoark","CreatedById":57151,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-09-16T21:04:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI played for awhile IVA-only, using Kerbal Engineer. Deployed a few RemoteTech satellites, built a 4-part station, and a Mun landing.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}